# PHPUnit — coverage: @covers and attributes (HIVE003)

Reference: `architecture/hive/HIVE003-phpunit-testing-standards.md`, [PHPUnit Code Coverage](https://docs.phpunit.de/en/10.5/code-coverage.html)

## Rule

Each test class **must** explicitly declare what it covers:

- **Unit tests** targeting **a single** production class: use **`#[CoversClass(ClassName::class)]`** on the test class.
- **Functional, integration, or multi-component tests**: use **`#[CoversNothing]`**.

Prefer **PHP 8 attributes** over `@covers` / `@coversNothing` annotations.

## Attributes (PHP 8)

Namespace: `PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes`.

| Annotation       | Equivalent attribute                         |
|------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| `@coversNothing` | `#[CoversNothing]`                           |
| `@covers \X\Y\Z`| `#[CoversClass(\X\Y\Z::class)]`              |
| (method)         | `#[CoversMethod(ClassName::class, 'method')]`|

## Compliant examples

### Unit test — single target class

```php
use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\CoversClass;
use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;

#[CoversClass(MyService::class)]
final class MyServiceTest extends TestCase
{
    // ...
}
```

### Functional / integration test

```php
use PHPUnit\Framework\Attributes\CoversNothing;
use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;

/**
 * @internal
 */
#[CoversNothing]
final class ApiIntegrationTest extends TestCase
{
    // ...
}
```

### Multiple covered classes (repeatable)

```php
#[CoversClass(Foo::class)]
#[CoversClass(Bar::class)]
final class FooAndBarTest extends TestCase
{
    // ...
}
```

## Effects

- **Documentation**: immediately shows which class is under test.
- **Coverage**: with `requireCoverageMetadata="true"` (optional), PHPUnit only attributes coverage to declared classes.
- **Infection**: metadata helps map tests to mutated code.

## Migration

- Replace `@coversNothing` with `#[CoversNothing]` (strict equivalent).
- Replace `@covers \Namespace\Class` with `#[CoversClass(\Namespace\Class::class)]`.
- For unit tests currently on `@coversNothing` that only exercise **one** class, prefer `#[CoversClass(ThatClass::class)]`.
